Subject: Only use stdint.h if it's present.

MSVC2008 is missing stdint.h and other C99 headers. win32_rasqal_config.h is
already declaring typedefs for the needed integer types, but some source files
still include stdint.h unconditionally. This patch makes them include stdint.h
only if HAVE_STDINT_H is defined.

Author: Nicol√°s Alvarez <nicolas.alvarez@gmail.com>
Last-Update: 2013-09-07

diff -Nru -x '*~' rasqal-0.9.30.orig/src/rasqal_digest_md5.c rasqal-0.9.30/src/rasqal_digest_md5.c
--- rasqal-0.9.30.orig/src/rasqal_digest_md5.c	2012-02-10 20:41:11.000000000 -0300
+++ rasqal-0.9.30/src/rasqal_digest_md5.c	2013-09-07 21:38:29.652048800 -0300
@@ -50,8 +50,10 @@
 
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include <string.h>
-#include <stdint.h>
 #include <stdarg.h>
+#ifdef HAVE_STDINT_H
+#include <stdint.h>
+#endif
 
 #include "rasqal.h"
 #include "rasqal_internal.h"
